**Problem**: Each sub-hive is queried sequentially. With 10 sub-hives, this creates blocking I/O delays.

**Solution**: Use `Promise.all()` for parallel execution:

```typescript
// OPTIMIZED: Parallel queries with error handling
const queries = subHivePorts.map(port =>
  getFromHive(port, "/swarm/agents")
    .then(agents => ({ port, agents, success: true }))
    .catch(err => {
      console.warn(`[swarm-router] failed to query sub-hive on port ${port}:`, err.message || err);
      return { port, agents: [], success: false };
    })
);

const results = await Promise.all(queries);

for (const { port, agents, success } of results) {
  if (success && Array.isArray(agents)) {
    for (const agent of agents) {
      routingTable.set(agent.id, {
        hiveId: agent.hiveId || "unknown",
        hivePort: port,
        agentName: agent.profileName || agent.id,
        profileName: agent.profileName,
        profileIcon: agent.profileIcon,
      });
      // ... handle terminalId
    }
  }
}
```

**Impact**: Reduces routing table refresh time from `O(n × latency)` to `O(max_latency)` — **~10x faster** with 10 sub-hives.

